  "stimulus_html": "<p>Iodine azide, IN<sub>3</sub>, adds to alkenes by an electrophilic mechanism similar to that of bromine. If a monosubstituted alkene such as 1-butene is used, only one product results:</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBblVTIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--40c1fe3a05a8671bdd14dedadf340dfc6468448c/OChem_08_EC_024.jpg\" alt=\"A reaction shows 1-butene reacting with iodine azide to form product where C1 of butane is bonded to iodine an C2 is bonded to the azide group.\">",
